<h3>Tech Questions</h3>
<hr>
<h4>Q: What is this ? Is it another computer game or something?</h4>
<p>Yes, its a game, Yes, there are computers involved, but No ... its neither of the above !</p>
<p>This is a completely analog Tabletop Miniatures Game ... in the full traditional sense - with miniatures, scenery, tapes and rulers, and players who must interact face to face.</p>
<p>The "Computer" part of it takes on the role of a sort of combined Game Umpire / Bookkeeper for the action on the tabletop. Its there to assist, handle the information flow, and manage the bookkeeping.</p>
<p>Each player uses their own computer device (laptop / phone / tablet), to interact with the "Computer Umpire" using a standard Web Browser interface whilst playing the game.<p>
<p>So, not a computer game .. but a computer-assisted miniatures game, with a web interface.</p>

<hr>
<h4>Q: So what sort of computers are supported?</h4>
<p>Being a "web based" application, you NEED a reasonably reliable internet connection to run this as well.</p>
<p>Anything reasonably modern, running a modern web browser. Ideally something light and portable with a good screen and reasonable grunt.</p>
<p>Game play involves clicking on options that are presented, so Touch Screen devices and tablets work well for game play.</p>
<p>Game setup involves some typing and data entry, so a Keyboard equipped device works well for game setup.</p>
<p>In other words, if you can read this FAQ, then you have everything you need to be able to join a game.</p>
<p>Any of the following types of machines should work fine :</p>
<ul>
	<li><i class="fa fa-android fa-lg"></i> Android .. works fine on Android phones and tablets.</li>
	<li><i class="fa fa-chrome fa-lg"></i> Chromebooks are perfect for this app, especially the lightweight models with touchscreens.</li>
	<li><i class="fa fa-apple fa-lg"></i> Macbooks, iPads, iPhone .. All tested to work fine using Safari and Chrome.</li>
	<li><i class="fa fa-linux fa-lg"></i> Linux (or BSD) machine running Firefox / Chrome, or any modern browser really.</li>
	<li><i class="fa fa-windows fa-lg"></i> Windows machine running a modern browser - IE Edge, Firefox, Chrome, etc. Old versions of IE will simply not work.</li>
</ul>
<p></p>

<hr>
<h4>Q: What are the Multi-User Aspects and Limitations?</h4>
<p>Each Game played on the system can have a number of Players connect to that game at the same time .. but this number is limited based on the Rank of the Player who is hosting the Game.</p>
<p>The Free Account allows you to setup and run games with 2 players connected at the same time.</p>
<p>The Higher Ranking Commissions allows you setup and run games with more players - up to a maximum of 16 players at the same time.</p>

 
<hr>
<h4>Q: Tell me about the Network Requirements for game play?</h4>
<p>If you are on a wired or dedicated WiFi connection in your game room, then you are fine .. so lets look at 3G or 4G mobile connections in more detail, as being the extreme worst case scenario.</p>
<p>For each player that connects to the system, it will use between 4-10 MB Total bandwidth to connect and load all the game assets.</p>
<p>Once connected, the connection stays open to improve latency / speed, and from there the data bandwidth used is minimal .. 2-3 MB total data usage for a 2-3 hour game.</p>
<p>If the optional Audio Effects are used in a game, then expect another 5-10 MB data usage per player per game.</p>
<p>If your mobile coverage is patchy where you are playing, then players may need to re-connect each time that the network drops out, requiring the initial data to be loaded again, which will be another 2-4MB each time this happens. (Note - its less each time due to caching.)</p>
<p>Thats all the tech stuff anyway, for those that are counting beans and worried about burning through your bandwidth on your mobile account.</p>
<p>Bottom line - as a good Game Host, you should provide not only a healthy supply of Beer and Pretzels for your fellow Gentlemen and Officers ... but also a reasonable Wifi connection as a bare minimum, if you are going to use this system :)</p>

